Part 3: Modeling continued...¶

Adding dummies and test/train split¶

In [2]:
flights = pd.read_feather('flights.feather')

# adding dummies for seasons and day of week
seasons = pd.get_dummies(flights['season'], prefix = 'season')
day_of_week = pd.get_dummies(flights['day_of_week'], prefix = 'day_of_week')

flights = pd.concat([flights, seasons], join = 'outer', axis = 1)
flights = pd.concat([flights, day_of_week], join = 'outer', axis = 1)
flights = flights.drop(columns = ['day_of_week', 'season'])
In [3]:
train = flights[flights['date'].dt.year < 2017]
test = flights[flights['date'].dt.year == 2017]

train = train.drop(columns = ['date'])
test = test.drop(columns = ['date'])

train_y = train['count'].to_numpy()
test_y = test['count'].to_numpy()

train = train.drop(columns = ['count'])
test = test.drop(columns = ['count'])

train_x = train.values
test_x = test.values

# unsure how to use scaler here, different results for when scaled versus not
scaler = StandardScaler()
scaled_train_x = scaler.fit_transform(train_x)

pred_y = lr.predict(test_x)

Part 4: Forecast Future Faily Flight Counts¶

In [22]:
df = flights[["date", "count"]].copy(True)
n_training = len(df)

forecast = 365 # days
end_date = df['date'][len(df) - 1]
forecast_dates = [end_date + dt.timedelta(days=d + 1) for d in range(forecast)]
forecast_values = [None for d in range (forecast)]

forecast_df = pd.DataFrame({
    "date" : forecast_dates,
    "count" : forecast_values
})

df = pd.concat([df, forecast_df], ignore_index = False)
df.reset_index(inplace = True, drop = True)

# adding elapsed days to flight
first_date = flights['date'][0]
df['elapsed_days'] = df['date'].apply(lambda d: (d-first_date).days)

df['month'] = df['date'].dt.month
df['day_of_week'] = df['date'].dt.dayofweek

df['season'] = df['date'].dt.month%12 // 3 + 1

dum_month = pd.get_dummies(df['month'], prefix = 'month')
dum_weekday = pd.get_dummies(df['day_of_week'], prefix = 'day_of_week')
dum_season = pd.get_dummies(df['season'], prefix = 'season')

df = df.merge(dum_month, left_index = True, right_index = True)
df = df.merge(dum_weekday, left_index = True, right_index = True)
df = df.merge(dum_season, left_index = True, right_index = True)
